			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<b><strong>Kaltura</strong></b></p>
<p>
Founded in 2006, Kaltura provides the world&rsquo;s first Open Source Online Video Platform, transforming the way people work, learn, and entertain using online video. The Kaltura platform engages hundreds of millions of viewers by providing media companies advanced video management, publishing, and monetization tools that increase their reach and monetization and simplify their video operations. Kaltura improves productivity and interaction among millions of employees by providing enterprises powerful online video tools for boosting internal knowledge sharing, training, and collaboration, and for more effective marketing. Kaltura offers next generation learning for millions of students and teachers by providing educational institutions disruptive online video solutions for improved teaching, learning, and increased engagement across campuses and beyond.</p>
<p>
<b><strong>Recognition:</strong></b></p>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>Forbes</strong> recognized Kaltura as &lsquo;one of six fast growing tech companies&rsquo; and as &lsquo;pegged to become a billion dollar company&rsquo;</li>
<li>
<strong>Inc. Magazine</strong> recognized Kaltura as &lsquo;on target to become the next billion dollar video company&rsquo;</li>
<li>
<strong>VentureBeat</strong> recognized Kaltura as a &lsquo;next billion dollar enterprise tech company&rsquo;, and as&nbsp; &lsquo;one of 5 fastest growing Israeli startups&rsquo;</li>
<li>
<strong>Huffington Post</strong> recognized Kaltura as &lsquo;one of five great tech companies to watch in 2013&rsquo;</li>
<li>
<strong>Business-Insider</strong> recognized Kaltura as &lsquo;one of top 5 startups revolutionizing education&rsquo;, &lsquo;one of 5 greatest open-source technologies for 2012&rsquo;, and as &lsquo;one of 5 fastest growing startups of 2012&rsquo;</li>
<li>
<strong>Mashable</strong> recognized Kaltura as &lsquo;one of top 5 social enterprise technologies for business&rsquo;</li>
</ul>
<p>
<u><strong>Solutions Architect:</strong></u></p>
<p>
This is a high-impact opportunity for someone with excellent business acumen, well-honed technical skills and a proven track record of operating in a fast-paced, multi-tasking work environment where flexibility is essential and excellence is a given. In this role, you will have the opportunity to work with a hard-working entrepreneurial team and to lead new integrations via the necessary software development lifecycle.</p>
<p>
The Solution Architect is a dynamic, hands-on role that works closely with the Kaltura sales, business development, marketing and product development teams, as well as the broader Kaltura community. You are responsible for crafting and representing Kaltura&rsquo;s online video solutions in the market, and serve as the subject matter expert during the pre-sale and post-sale process working closely with the customers to scope and define the best technical solutions to their business needs.</p>
<p>
<strong>Duties and responsibilities include but are not limited to:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Own technical communications with prospects including solution demonstration, responding to RFP/RFI and training over a Web conference or onsite.</li>
<li>
Serve as architect and consult with account team to develop architectural solutions for customers.</li>
<li>
Provide technical pre-sales and solution engineering support to Kaltura representatives, documenting customer use cases and technical requirements and then proposing a unified solution</li>
<li>
Maintain current and in-depth knowledge of the entire Kaltura platform and offerings.</li>
<li>
Lead design sessions with strategic clients, detailing high level design plans to the Kaltura team through specifications, site diagrams, and wireframes.</li>
<li>
Strategically engage the broader technology and developer community, identifying new business development, sales, and developer opportunities</li>
<li>
Consult existing clients to review use of Kaltura products and identify up sell opportunities</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Skills and Qualifications:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Graduate degree preferred, in Computer Science, Technology, Media, or Information Systems</li>
<li>
5+ years of experience, preferably in SaaS technology</li>
<li>
Demonstrated leadership and experience in technical pre-sales, product, product marketing, or complex software sales at a leading technology company</li>
<li>
Experience leading design sessions, documenting use cases, and proposing software solutions for Web and distributed systems</li>
<li>
Excellent speaking, presentation, and writing skills</li>
<li>
Ability to create product marketing materials in standard software programs</li>
<li>
Ability to articulate value proposition, focusing on selling business outcomes and not just technology solutions.</li>
<li>
Excellent organizational skills and strong attention to detail</li>
<li>
Candidate must be results-oriented, proactive, self-motivated and work well in a team environment</li>
<li>
Must be comfortable working within a dynamic, changing, and challenging environment where everyone &quot;does it all&quot;, and work extensive and unconventional hours</li>
<li>
Familiar with technology including but not limited to: cloud computing, open source technologies, mobile platforms, digital video, and infrastructure design</li>
<li>
Must be willing to travel &ndash; domestically and internationally</li>
<li>
Intimate knowledge of the Media &amp; entertainment domain</li>
<li>
Background in web publishing and development, HTML, PHP, CMSs (Drupal, Wordpress, Moodle etc), a major advantage. Knowledge and experience with web-based video delivery, infrastructure, streaming, transcoding and optimization an asset.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>We offer a comprehensive benefits and compensation package complete with Medical, Dental, Vision, Life/ADD, Disability, Commuter, Flexible Spending &amp; Retirement benefits.</strong></p>
<p>
Thank you for your interest, we look forward to hearing from you.</p>
<p>
#opensource#video</p>
