<strong><u>Sales Engineer:</u></strong></p>
<p>
The Sales Engineer is a dynamic, hands-on role that works closely with the Kaltura sales, business development, marketing and product development teams, as well as the broader Kaltura community.&nbsp; You are responsible for crafting and representing Kaltura&#39;s Enterprise/ SMB solutions in the market, and serve as the subject matter expert during the pre-sale and post-sale process working closely with the customers to scope and define the best solution to their business needs.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities include:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Serve as a liaison between the product and sales teams, educating current and future Kaltura Enterprise/SMB clients on our product suite</li>
<li>
Serve as architect and consult with account team to develop architectural solutions for customers.</li>
<li>
Maintain current and in-depth knowledge of the entire Kaltura product line.</li>
<li>
Provide technical pre-sales and solution engineering support to Kaltura representatives, documenting customer use cases and technical requirements and then proposing a unified solution</li>
<li>
Demonstrate Kaltura products both over the web and at client sites</li>
<li>
Lead design sessions with strategic Enterprise/SMB clients, detailing high level design plans to the Kaltura team through specifications, site diagrams, and wireframes.</li>
<li>
Provide input to the Enterprise/SMB team lead and the Kaltura VP of Product on the Enterprise/SMB product roadmap</li>
<li>
Represent Kaltura at conferences and community events, through speaking engagements, blogging, and participation on list-serves</li>
<li>
Strategically engage the broader enterprise technology and developer community, identifying new business development, sales, and developer opportunities</li>
<li>
Create support materials and documentation for Kaltura products and develop training courses for Kaltura University</li>
<li>
Provide on site training for strategic Enterprise/SMB clients</li>
<li>
Consult existing clients to review use of Kaltura products and identify up sell opportunities</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Desired Skills &amp; Experience:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Graduate degree preferred, in Computer Science, Technology, Media, or Information Systems</li>
<li>
5+ years of experience, preferably in SaaS technology</li>
<li>
Demonstrated leadership and experience in technical pre-sales, product, product marketing, or complex software sales at a leading technology company</li>
<li>
Experience leading design sessions, documenting use cases, and proposing software solutions for Web and distributed systems</li>
<li>
Excellent speaking, presentation, and writing skills</li>
<li>
Ability to create product marketing materials in standard software programs</li>
<li>
Ability to articulate value proposition, focusing on selling business outcomes and not just technology solutions.</li>
<li>
Excellent organizational skills and strong attention to detail</li>
<li>
Candidate must be results-oriented, pro-active, self-motivated and work well in a team environment</li>
<li>
Must be comfortable working within a dynamic, changing, and challenging environment where everyone &quot;does it all&quot;, and work extensive and unconventional hours</li>
<li>
Familiar with technology including but not limited to: cloud computing, open source technologies, mobile platforms, digital video, and infrastructure design</li>
<li>
Must be willing to travel &ndash; domestically and internationally</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>We offer a comprehensive benefits and compensation package complete with Medical, Dental, Vision, Life/ADD, Disability, Commuter, Flexible Spending &amp; Retirement benefits.</strong></p>
<p>
<strong>Thank you for your interest, we look forward to hearing from you.</strong></p>
